OL,3,CHead accountant jailed after stealing
OL,4,C#130k from own firm
OL,6,FA head accountant for a top firm has
OL,7,Fbeen jailed after she took "carefully
OL,8,Fplanned steps" to defraud her company
OL,9,Fout of close to #130,000.
OL,11,FNicola Clarke had been abusing her
OL,12,Fposition at the Stockport-based firm
OL,13,FBusiness Computer Projects Ltd since
OL,14,F2008 to steal in "discreet ways."
OL,16,FMinshull Street Crown Court heard that
OL,17,Fthe 56-year-old had spent more than a
OL,18,Fdecade claiming unauthorised overtime
OL,19,Fpayments, stealing petty cash, and
OL,20,Fusing the company's credit card
OL,21,Fwithout permission.
