OL,3,CHead accountant jailed after stealing
OL,4,C#130k from own firm
OL,6,FClarke, who had worked for the company
OL,7,Fsince 1987, was found out in June 2019
OL,8,Fwhen it was discovered she was using
OL,9,Fthe credit card. At the time, she
OL,10,Fclaimed she had been using it for six
OL,11,Fmonths and promised to pay the company
OL,12,Fback, but she later accepted she had
OL,13,Fbeen defrauding her employer for 11
OL,14,Fyears.
OL,16,FA full investigation took place which
OL,17,Frevealed the full extent of Clarke's
OL,18,Fdishonesty. She pleaded guilty at an
OL,19,Fearlier hearing to three charges of
OL,20,Ffraud by abuse of position and was
OL,21,Fjailed for 18 months.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/9
