OL,3,CHead accountant jailed after stealing
OL,4,C#130k from own firm
OL,6,FPierce Power, prosecuting, said Clarke
OL,7,Fhad claimed a number of overtime
OL,8,Fpayments, but they were not
OL,9,Fauthorised, nor did she request for
OL,10,Fthem to be authorised.
OL,12,FHe said: "She paid herself overtime
OL,13,Fwithout any paperwork - and took
OL,14,Fcareful steps to avoid getting caught."
OL,16,FAs the head of accounts, Clarke held
OL,17,Fsole responsibility for all of the
OL,18,Ffinancial aspects of the company.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/9
