OL,3,CHead accountant jailed after stealing
OL,4,C#130k from own firm
OL,6,FThe court heard that all purchases
OL,7,Fover #50 had to have a signature from
OL,8,Fa director and the rules of the card
OL,9,Fprohibited personal spending without
OL,10,Fprior confirmation.
OL,12,FClarke had taken "carefully planned
OL,13,Fsteps" to hide her use of the card,
OL,14,Fand had even forged the signature on
OL,15,Fat least two occasions.
OL,17,FIn total, the amount of overtime she
OL,18,Fpaid to herself was #15,746; the
OL,19,Famount of petty cash taken was #7,959,
OL,20,Fand the amount spent on the credit
OL,21,Fcard was #104,647.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
